Hello,
When considering  use_snes_vi_solver in  ComputeLinearElasticPFFractureStress.C, I think that it does not work properly when we do have _barrier : the damage is negatif at the biginning of the simulation until barrier reached.  The block that assigns history variable is :
// // Assign history variable
  Real hist_variable = _H_old[_qp];
  if (_use_snes_vi_solver)
  {
    _H[_qp] = F_pos;

    if (_use_current_hist)
      hist_variable = _H[_qp];
  }
  else
  {
    if (F_pos > _H_old[_qp])
      _H[_qp] = F_pos;
    else
      _H[_qp] = _H_old[_qp];

    if (_use_current_hist)
      hist_variable = _H[_qp];

    if (hist_variable < _barrier[_qp])
     hist_variable = _barrier[_qp];
  }  

I think that the two last instructions should be put outside like this:
// // Assign history variable
  Real hist_variable = _H_old[_qp];
  if (_use_snes_vi_solver)
  {
    _H[_qp] = F_pos;

    if (_use_current_hist)
      hist_variable = _H[_qp];
  }
  else
  {
    if (F_pos > _H_old[_qp])
      _H[_qp] = F_pos;
    else
      _H[_qp] = _H_old[_qp];

    if (_use_current_hist)
      hist_variable = _H[_qp];
// Original
//    if (hist_variable < _barrier[_qp])
 //     hist_variable = _barrier[_qp];
  }  
  //  Correction 11/01/2024
  if (hist_variable < _barrier[_qp])
                hist_variable = _barrier[_qp];

regards,
saber

There's another problem that we have observed concerning the bandwidth of the damaged zone: when a barrier is considered in the case of linear fracture energy (3/8 *  gc /Lc  * d) the band width is theoretically 4 * Lc (Lc being the internal  length scale). This will never be obtained in the actual implementation in moose!  The instruction : hist_variable = _barrier[_qp]; should never be executed means invoked. This used to happen (before our correction suggestion) when _use_snes_vi_solver = true (and the correct bounds for the Executioner block).
So in summary, the older version was fine in the unique case of    considering a barrier and using snes solver.  When  _use_snes_vi_solver = false;  the bandwidth could be 20*Lc.
with the correction we have suggested, whenever we have a barrier (with or without use of the snes solver) , the bandwidth is too large.
So in case of linear fracture energy, the snes solver has to be mandatory.  So the code should be something like this:
 if (_barrier)
_use_snes_vi_solver = true; 

if (_use_snes_vi_solver)
  {
    _H[_qp] = F_pos;

    if (_use_current_hist)
      hist_variable = _H[_qp];
  }
